		{"id":"a6010c0a6a11ce26","x":-640,"y":-400,"width":405,"height":1060,"type":"text","text":"For the vibration/cymatics side, here are search terms that'll pull good imagery:\n\nDirect:\n\n• cymatics photography\n• Chladni figures\n• sand pattern vibration\n• standing wave patterns\n• acoustic levitation\n\nNature parallels:\n\n• brain coral macro\n• sand dune ripples aerial\n• fingerprint macro photography\n• muscle fiber cross-section\n• sound frequency water surface\n\nScientific/technical:\n\n• resonance frequency visualization\n• acoustic holography\n• Faraday wave patterns\n• vibration mode shapes\n\nFor the \"same math\" angle:\n\n• Turing patterns biology\n• reaction-diffusion patterns\n• morphogenesis patterns\n• self-organizing systems photography\n\nThe sweet spot for your collage is probably Chladni figures + brain coral + sand dunes — those three have the most visual rhyme. They all have that radiating-from-center, find-the-path-of-least-resistance quality. Faraday waves are also stunning if you want something more liquid and flowing.\n\nIf you're going black and white, Chladni figures are unbeatable.\n"}
